drops by 0.01 every two epochs. The sampled participants mt are Ô¨Åxed with 20. At each communication round, the participants‚Äô models are trained individually and distributedly before being averaged into the global model. We choose a similar process of MNIST dataset as [4] and [12], where the whole dataset was divided into 10 shards and each client got two shards. The training accuracy and loss results are shown in Fig. 4, we can see that the accuracy with our PEFL setting is very close to the accuracy with no privacy setting, which means our PEFL can integrate cryptographic method in federated learning system without sacriÔ¨Åce too much model accuracy.
